Those cars probably don't have an oil cooler, either, but I don't think
that this would be a good reason to remove the cooler from a VW!

Are you aware of the transmission problems on Odysseys?  Honda is
extending the warranty, but doesn't seem to want to fix the problem
through a proper recall.  Something to keep an eye on...

> Anyone out there want to weld some fins to the steel covers (except those
> darn bails get in the way) and see if the head temps go down?

A simpler way would be simply to spray water on the outer surface of the
cover and watch the head temps.  The water absorbs a lot more heat than
any finning would and would give a quick indication of how much heat can
be lost via this route.  I doubt that the temp drop would be great, even
with "water cooled" covers.

George
